    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="856"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d856">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 EW/7–2944</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The First Secretary of the British Embassy</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gore-Booth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Legal Adviser</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hackworth</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-29">29 July,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Hackworth</hi>: With reference to the meeting
                    which took place in your office on July 7th at which was discussed the draft of
                    a directive to Military commanders in the field on the subject of treatment of
                    war criminals, I am glad to inform you that we have now heard from the Foreign
                    Office that they approve the draft which we agreed on that occasion.</p>
                <p>I am sending you two extra copies of this letter for your convenience in
                    informing the War and Navy Departments.</p>
                <p>This Embassy is also communicating with the British Secretariat of the Combined
                    Chiefs of Staff in order that preparations may be made for the issue of the
                    agreed directive provided that the final concurrence of the United States
                    Government authorities concerned is forthcoming.</p>
                <p>Yours sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paul Gore-Booth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
